## 03 — Pre-Build Checklist for Antigravity

Complete all of the following before building a single node.

### 3.1 View Verification
- [ ] `vw_mr_report_payload` exists in Supabase
- [ ] Query with a test `assessment_id` returns exactly one row with all 130 columns populated and no NULLs
- [ ] Confirm column names exactly match the `{{MERGE_FIELD}}` token names in the Google Doc template (case-sensitive)

### 3.2 Google Configuration
- [ ] Google service account credential is added to n8n with name `google_docs_api` (or confirm the exact name used in your n8n instance)
- [ ] Service account has Editor access to the master template Google Doc
- [ ] Service account has write access to the designated report output folder in Google Drive
- [ ] Master template Google Doc ID is confirmed and noted (extract from the doc URL: `docs.google.com/document/d/[DOC_ID]/edit`)
- [ ] Report output folder ID is confirmed and noted (extract from Drive folder URL)

### 3.3 Supabase Storage
- [ ] Bucket for PDF storage is confirmed (name and path prefix, e.g. `reports/mr/`)
- [ ] Bucket RLS policy allows the service role to insert and generate signed URLs
- [ ] Signed URL expiry duration is decided (recommended: 7 days, renewable on re-trigger)

### 3.4 Report Template Record
- [ ] `gm_report_templates` has a row for the M+R PDF template with:
  - `template_id`: e.g. `mr_pdf_v1`
  - `template_type`: `pdf`
  - `template_version`: `1`
  - `storage_bucket`: the Google Doc ID or a reference identifier
  - `is_active`: `true`

