## 04 — Workflow Architecture

### Trigger
POST webhook receiving `{ "assessment_id": "uuid" }` — fired by the frontend "Download Full Report" button action or manually.

### Node Sequence

```
01  Webhook
02  Code — Validate Input
03  Respond to Webhook (202)
04  Supabase — Check WF-MR-01 Complete
05  Supabase — Check WF-MR-02 Complete
06  Code — Validate Dependencies
07  Supabase — Fetch Report Payload (vw_mr_report_payload)
08  Code — Build Merge Map
09  Google Drive — Copy Template Doc
10  Code — Build Find-Replace Operations
11  Google Docs — Batch Update (Find & Replace)
12  Google Drive — Export as PDF
13  Code — Validate PDF Binary
14  Supabase Storage — Upload PDF
15  Code — Build Artifact Record
16  Supabase — Insert gm_report_artifacts
17  Code — Generate Signed URL
18  Supabase — Update gm_assessments reported_at
19  [Error Handler] Code — Error Handler
20  [Error Handler] Supabase — Write Failed Artifact Record
```

### Node Standards
Follow WF-MR-01 and WF-MR-02 standards exactly:
- **Supabase reads/writes:** Supabase nodes only, credential `Supabase account`
- **Google operations:** Google Docs node and Google Drive node only, credential `google_docs_api`
- **Logic and data transformation:** Code nodes only
- **No Function nodes, no HTTP Request nodes for Google APIs**

---

## 05 — Node Specifications

### Node 01 — Webhook
- Method: POST
- Path: `wf-mr-03`
- Response mode: `responseNode`

### Node 02 — Code: Validate Input
```javascript
const body = $input.first().json;
if (!body.assessment_id || typeof body.assessment_id !== 'string') {
  throw new Error('Missing or invalid assessment_id');
}
return [{ json: { assessment_id: body.assessment_id.trim() } }];
```

### Node 03 — Respond to Webhook
- HTTP 202
- Body: `{ "status": "accepted", "message": "Report generation initiated", "assessment_id": "..." }`

### Node 04 — Supabase: Check WF-MR-01 Complete
- Operation: `getAll`
- Table: `gm_gpt_runs`
- Filter: `assessment_id = [assessment_id]` AND `slot_id = 'mr_hero_headline'` AND `run_status = 'complete'`
- Limit: 1

### Node 05 — Supabase: Check WF-MR-02 Complete
- Operation: `getAll`
- Table: `gm_gpt_runs`
- Filter: `assessment_id = [assessment_id]` AND `slot_id = 'mr_pdf_tldr_headline'` AND `run_status = 'complete'`
- Limit: 1

### Node 06 — Code: Validate Dependencies
```javascript
const mr01 = $('Supabase — Check WF-MR-01 Complete').all();
const mr02 = $('Supabase — Check WF-MR-02 Complete').all();
const assessmentId = $('Code — Validate Input').first().json.assessment_id;

if (mr01.length === 0) {
  throw new Error('WF-MR-01 not complete for assessment_id: ' + assessmentId + '. Cannot generate PDF until GPT synthesis is finished.');
}
if (mr02.length === 0) {
  throw new Error('WF-MR-02 not complete for assessment_id: ' + assessmentId + '. Cannot generate PDF until PDF synthesis is finished.');
}
return [{ json: { assessment_id: assessmentId } }];
```

### Node 07 — Supabase: Fetch Report Payload
- Operation: `getAll`
- Table: `vw_mr_report_payload`
- Filter: `assessment_id = [assessment_id]`
- Limit: 1

### Node 08 — Code: Build Merge Map
Converts the flat view row into an array of `{ token, value }` pairs ready for the Google Docs batch update.

```javascript
const payload = $('Supabase — Fetch Report Payload').first().json;
const assessmentId = $('Code — Validate Dependencies').first().json.assessment_id;

if (!payload) {
  throw new Error('No report payload found for assessment_id: ' + assessmentId);
}

// Build find-replace pairs from all payload columns
// Each key in the view row becomes a {{KEY}} token
const mergeMap = Object.entries(payload)
  .filter(([key]) => key !== 'assessment_id') // exclude the ID itself
  .map(([key, value]) => ({
    find: '{{' + key + '}}',
    replace: value !== null && value !== undefined ? String(value) : ''
  }));

return [{ json: { assessment_id: assessmentId, merge_map: mergeMap, payload } }];
```

### Node 09 — Google Drive: Copy Template Doc
- Operation: Copy file
- File ID: `[MASTER_TEMPLATE_DOC_ID]` (hardcoded — confirmed in pre-build checklist)
- Destination folder: `[REPORT_OUTPUT_FOLDER_ID]` (hardcoded)
- New file name: `MR_Report_{{ payload.RESPONDENT_NAME }}_{{ payload.ASSESSMENT_DATE }}`

> Antigravity: The Google Drive node copy operation returns the new file's ID. Pass this as `copied_doc_id` to subsequent nodes.

### Node 10 — Code: Build Find-Replace Operations
Transforms the merge map into the Google Docs API `batchUpdate` request body format.

```javascript
const data = $input.first().json;
const mergeMap = data.merge_map;
const copiedDocId = $('Google Drive — Copy Template Doc').first().json.id;

// Build Google Docs batchUpdate replaceAllText operations
const requests = mergeMap.map(item => ({
  replaceAllText: {
    containsText: {
      text: item.find,
      matchCase: true
    },
    replaceText: item.replace
  }
}));

return [{ json: {
  ...data,
  copied_doc_id: copiedDocId,
  batch_update_body: { requests }
}}];
```

### Node 11 — Google Docs: Batch Update (Find & Replace)
- Operation: Update document (batchUpdate)
- Document ID: `={{ $json.copied_doc_id }}`
- Request body: `={{ $json.batch_update_body }}`

> This single node executes all find-and-replace operations across the entire document in one API call. All `{{TOKEN}}` placeholders are replaced with their resolved values.

### Node 12 — Google Drive: Export as PDF
- Operation: Download/Export file
- File ID: `={{ $json.copied_doc_id }}`
- Export MIME type: `application/pdf`

> Returns binary PDF data. Pass to Node 13 for validation before upload.

### Node 13 — Code: Validate PDF Binary
```javascript
const binaryData = $input.first().binary;
if (!binaryData || !binaryData.data) {
  throw new Error('PDF export failed — no binary data returned from Google Drive export.');
}
const sizeBytes = Buffer.from(binaryData.data, 'base64').length;
if (sizeBytes < 10000) {
  throw new Error('PDF export appears incomplete — file size too small: ' + sizeBytes + ' bytes.');
}
return [{ 
  json: { 
    ...$input.first().json,
    pdf_size_bytes: sizeBytes 
  }, 
  binary: binaryData 
}];
```

### Node 14 — Supabase Storage: Upload PDF
- Operation: Upload
- Bucket: `[STORAGE_BUCKET_NAME]`
- File path: `mr_reports/{{ assessment_id }}/mr_report_{{ assessment_id }}.pdf`
- Binary property: PDF binary from Node 12/13
- Upsert: true (allows re-generation to overwrite)

> Returns the storage path. Use for signed URL generation and artifact record.

### Node 15 — Code: Build Artifact Record
```javascript
const data = $('Code — Validate PDF Binary').first().json;
const uploadResult = $('Supabase Storage — Upload PDF').first().json;
const now = new Date().toISOString();
const expiresAt = new Date(Date.now() + 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString(); // 7 days

return [{ json: {
  assessment_id: data.assessment_id,
  template_id: 'mr_pdf_v1',
  artifact_type: 'pdf',
  artifact_status: 'complete',
  storage_bucket: '[STORAGE_BUCKET_NAME]',
  storage_path: uploadResult.path || uploadResult.Key || '',
  file_name: 'mr_report_' + data.assessment_id + '.pdf',
  mime_type: 'application/pdf',
  file_size_bytes: data.pdf_size_bytes,
  generated_at: now,
  expires_at: expiresAt,
  copied_doc_id: data.copied_doc_id
}}];
```

### Node 16 — Supabase: Insert gm_report_artifacts
- Operation: create (INSERT)
- Table: `gm_report_artifacts`
- Fields: all fields from Node 15 output
- Note: If a prior artifact row exists for this `assessment_id` + `template_id`, set prior row `artifact_status = 'superseded'` first, or use an update pattern. Antigravity to confirm preferred approach.

### Node 17 — Code: Generate Signed URL
```javascript
// The signed URL is generated via Supabase Storage API
// This node prepares the request parameters
const artifact = $input.first().json;
return [{ json: {
  ...artifact,
  artifact_id: $('Supabase — Insert gm_report_artifacts').first().json.artifact_id
}}];
```

> Antigravity: Supabase signed URL generation requires a call to the Supabase Storage API: `POST /storage/v1/object/sign/[bucket]/[path]` with `{ "expiresIn": 604800 }`. This can be done via an HTTP Request node pointing to your Supabase project URL with the service role key, or via a Supabase function. Confirm the approach with the existing credential setup and add the signed URL to `gm_report_artifacts.public_url` via an update node.

### Node 18 — Supabase: Update gm_assessments reported_at
- Operation: update
- Table: `gm_assessments`
- Filter: `assessment_id = [assessment_id]`
- Fields: `reported_at = now()`

### Node 19 — Code: Error Handler
```javascript
const error = $input.first();
const errorMsg = error.json ? (error.json.error || error.json.message || 'Unknown error') : 'Unknown error';

let assessment_id = null;
let copied_doc_id = null;
try { assessment_id = $('Code — Validate Input').first().json.assessment_id; } catch(e) {}
try { copied_doc_id = $('Code — Build Find-Replace Operations').first().json.copied_doc_id; } catch(e) {}

return [{ json: { error_message: errorMsg, assessment_id, copied_doc_id } }];
```

### Node 20 — Supabase: Write Failed Artifact Record
- Operation: create (INSERT) into `gm_report_artifacts`
- Fields: `assessment_id`, `template_id = 'mr_pdf_v1'`, `artifact_type = 'pdf'`, `artifact_status = 'failed'`, `error_message`, `storage_bucket = ''`, `storage_path = ''`, `generated_at = now()`

> Error handler nodes must be connected as error outputs from Nodes 07, 09, 11, 12, 13, and 14.

